# changelog

## 2026-06-26

- Added a standalone Stocktwits polling crawler MVP with staggered 10-ticker scheduling, per-ticker checkpoints, idempotent message persistence, crawl-run observability, gap detection, hot ticker mode, Supabase migration, CLI launchers, and focused regression tests.

## 2026-06-22

- Hardened A1 Document 2 construction-review DoxAtlas scope guardrails so proposition and ignored-proposition tools avoid invalid ticker/bare-narrative calls and finalize with explicit data gaps when event scope is unavailable.
- Fixed a Document 2 real-eval workflow stall where `ResolveExpectationConstruction` no-op completion still full-loaded oversized Blackboard run state for summary counts; Postgres now uses lightweight objection/delegation/count queries before continuing to detail generation.

## 2026-06-21

- Added deterministic daily OHLCV market-evidence snapshots to Twelve Data/yfinance results, ReAct scratchpad/final payloads, working memory, and global-research context so price/volume facts survive context compaction.
- Hardened ReAct compaction for daily OHLCV outputs with tool-aware summaries and tightened price-reaction promotion so narrative-only evidence cannot support market reaction claims without structured market-data snapshots.
- Reduced agent-visible working-memory payloads by summarizing prior ReAct/model/context audit data while preserving patch ids, tool usage, acceptance audit, structured summaries, and market-evidence snapshots.

## 2026-06-19

- Improved the Brief State Viewer's Document 2 expectation-unit display by rendering realized facts, key variables, and event monitoring direction as readable cards/lists while keeping evidence and raw JSON in collapsed details.
- Split labeled realized-fact description strings such as `fact`, `when`, `why_it_matters`, and `pricing_status` into separate readable fields in the Brief State Viewer instead of showing them as one merged paragraph.
- Added short Windows debug-viewer launchers under `scripts/` so the Brief State Viewer can be started with `scripts\debug-viewer.cmd 8765` or `.\scripts\debug-viewer.ps1 -Port 8765` while using repo-local uv cache/temp directories.
- Made the debug-viewer launchers auto-select the next free port when the requested port is already occupied, preventing stale SSH tunnels or old viewer processes from masking the current local UI.

## 2026-06-17

- Recorded MU Blackboard eval loop 4/5 (`run_dfd3a7c3eb8f481680be892871c509f6`) as a diagnostic incomplete run: numeric sanity blockers were correctly raised, but the run stopped during `ResolveObjectionsAndDelegations` after a Postgres disconnect and did not reach finalization.
- Added post-O1 numeric sanity revalidation so revised expectation patches are rescanned after objection resolution; same-id `numeric_sanity_*` objections are reopened when O1 keeps precise unsupported numbers under narrative-only, unverified, approximate, or uncertain labels.
- Strengthened O1 resolver guidance and deterministic numeric sanity objection reasons to require source-appropriate evidence, removal of false precision, or non-numeric uncertainty for precise market/fundamental claims.
- Added regression coverage for reopening a partially accepted numeric sanity objection when false precision remains after O1 revision, while preserving the existing source-appropriate market-data pass path.

## 2026-06-14

- Retested the MU Blackboard initialization follow-up optimization with a fresh real PostgreSQL-backed run (`run_a3f1618b088c4693875b87b735b4ea6f`), recorded hard-gate/rubric results, and identified remaining KnownEvents timestamp/flag quality gaps plus an O2 remote LangSmith trace visibility gap.
- Tightened KnownEvents normalization so run-timestamp-like event times are replaced by event-text/date hints, common quarter/FQ/year/date patterns are parsed, and `has_price_reaction` / `is_known_old_news` are inferred from explicit market/date signals.
- Cleaned ReAct realized-fact normalization so dict-shaped fact descriptions render as stable reviewable text instead of Python dict strings, with focused regression coverage for KnownEvents timestamp/flag inference and realized-fact description rendering.
- Fixed a real-eval BuildGlobalResearch blocking failure by adding configurable model request timeouts (`DOXAGENT_MODEL_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`) to the production runner, ReAct step/compaction requests, and MAF single-shot calls; recorded the blocked `run_c5a1b185a08a4f7ea639388081e23fb2` attempt and timeout verification tests.

## 2026-06-13

- Hardened the Blackboard initialization real-eval loop with stale-agent checkpoint recovery, workflow exception audit entries, non-vacuous hard validators, node-aware tool-boundary validation, global-research fallback content, evidence hydration for nested document refs, and direct-document Blackboard patch conversion.
- Localized eval-visible provider/runtime natural-language output to Chinese across DoxAtlas, SEC, Twelve Data, yfinance, Alpha Vantage, Tavily, FRED/Fed/BLS/BEA, Finnhub/FMP/Polymarket/AnySearch, tool registry errors, ReAct warnings, and direct document patch rationales while preserving tool names, tickers, schema keys, and raw source excerpts.
- Improved real-run robustness with SEC upstream-unavailable partial results, ticker/symbol alias handling for market-data tools, large ReAct observation compaction, expectation shell/detail normalization, objection resolution hardening, O1/A1 tool-boundary fixes, and multi-object JSON extraction in the gateway.
- Added run helpers and eval records for the MU Blackboard eval/debug loop, including hard-validator results, rubrics scoring, failure categories, optimization hypotheses, and retest records for `run_c3c4bab327ef49b8871fd59e57bfd593`, `run_acf56dd5e8a8490d83c0f85a207dfe18`, and `run_87d637922abe4672892bdf702d77e8bf`.
- Implemented the follow-up MU eval optimization plan's first two items only: expectation promotion now escalates unresolved `price_reaction` fields with O4/OHLCV market-trace evidence context, and KnownEvents normalization now infers expectation linkage, event-date hints, and source-specific evidence before falling back to agent-output provenance.

## 2026-06-12

- Hardened initialization quality contracts with structured MonitoringPolicy coverage gates, objection dedupe/resolution metadata, centralized required-output schema registration, node-specific tool allowlists with invented-tool evidence audit, A2 retrieval quality checks, LangSmith/business acceptance audit metadata, and prompt resource hygiene linting.

## 2026-06-07

- Configured LangSmith MCP server in `.mcp.json` with both `langsmith-hosted` (via Render endpoint with `LANGSMITH-API-KEY` header) and `langsmith-local` (via `uvx langsmith-mcp-server` command with local environment variables).

## 2026-06-03

- Added a local read-only Brief State debug viewer with a stdlib HTTP server, Supabase/Postgres run querying, document 1/document 2 review pages, and per-agent ReAct loop/tool/delegation/objection metrics.
- Added debug viewer view-model tests covering global research, expectation units, ReAct audit aggregation, missing audit handling, and secret redaction for rendered API payloads.
- Improved LangSmith trace readability with dynamic per-call run names, a local Custom Output Rendering page, and unified Simplified Chinese human-readable LLM output rules while preserving structured JSON contracts.
- Hardened the local LangSmith renderer endpoint for browser iframe loading with no-store responses, CORS/private-network preflight headers, and README troubleshooting notes for localhost and HTTPS tunnel usage.
- Suppressed expected local debug viewer client-disconnect noise, so browser refreshes, iframe reloads, and aborted JSON responses no longer print WinError 10053 tracebacks.
- Reworked the LangSmith Custom Renderer into a raw-first recursive JSON viewer that always displays metadata, metadata.inputs, outputs/data, and complete postMessage payloads before adding optional DoxAgent AgentResult/provider-response summaries.
- Made LangSmith run names monotonic per blackboard run/agent/workflow node by assigning a gateway-level `langsmith_loop_index`, and stopped real API smoke tests from forcing memory storage so Supabase-backed runs can appear in the Brief State Viewer.
- Reworked free-tier market-data tools by removing Alpha Vantage daily OHLCV and FMP press releases, adding Twelve Data daily OHLCV plus yfinance daily fallback, normalizing Tavily search depth, constraining FMP sector-performance parameters, and adding light SEC/FRED rate limiting with real smoke coverage.

