- Implemented P0 safe intra-node initialization parallelism: C1/C2/C3/O4 Global Research, per-shell O1 expectation details, and A1/C1/C3/O4 field reviews now fan out concurrently while Blackboard/checkpoint writes remain serialized and deterministic.
- Added parallel agent isolation, per-shell expectation-detail idempotency/cache recovery, main-thread schema failure auditing for parallel jobs, and regression coverage for concurrency, ordered merges, and failed-shell resume behavior.
- Filtered failed ReAct tool attempts out of successful AgentResult top-level `tool_calls` while retaining them in `react_audit`, and added ExpectationDetailResult text-array salvage for recoverable `realized_facts` / `key_variables` arrays with alias-aware fact, price-reaction, and variable normalization.
- Compacted O1 `ResolveObjectionsAndDelegations` resolver context by omitting full GlobalResearch replay and replacing full-size expectation context with schema-compatible compact pending patches plus lightweight patch indexes, preserving accepted-objection revision support while reducing resolver input size.
- Added task-aware ReAct output-contract guidance for field-review objection resolution so O1 resolver prompts request one decision per objection and avoid the normal expectation-construction instruction to generate 2-3 full patches unless a concrete accepted/partially accepted revision is required.
- Persisted parallel workflow agent outcomes as each future completes during BuildGlobalResearch so completed C1/C2/C3/O4 results are cached before aggregate completion, improving stale-dispatch recovery after a sibling job or parent process blocks.
- Increased pooled Postgres connection retry tolerance and made BuildGlobalResearch per-future checkpoint caching best-effort so transient pooler disconnects during auxiliary cache writes do not abort the whole workflow.
- Added operation-level Postgres retry handling for safe Blackboard reads/replacements and checkpoint reads/saves, with idempotent checkpoint upserts, so mid-query pooler SSL EOFs do not prevent real eval runs from starting or persisting checkpoints.
- Fixed ReAct parsing of Responses API payloads that wrap a JSON action inside `structured.text`, stopped accepting `is_complete=false` final payloads as successful results, and added a two-axis expectation-shell fallback for O1 construction recovery.
- Added bounded ReAct tool-call timeout handling with daemon-thread execution and settings-backed configuration so a stuck provider/tool call is recorded as a retryable failed ToolResult instead of blocking the agent future indefinitely.
- Added harness-level `asyncio.wait_for` enforcement around ReAct model and compaction requests so provider/SDK calls that ignore request timeout settings return retryable `model_request_timeout` errors instead of leaving workflow agent futures running.
- Added workflow-level wall-clock timeout handling for parallel initialization agent jobs so a stuck C1/C2/C3/O4 worker is recorded as `parallel_agent_timeout` instead of blocking `BuildGlobalResearch` indefinitely.
- Normalized KnownEvents real-agent outputs that use `event_date` and `event_text`, preventing stringified event dictionaries from entering stable event descriptions and preserving explicit no-price-reaction flags.
- Batched O1 objection resolution in `ResolveObjectionsAndDelegations` so high-review-pressure runs resolve small groups of objections instead of sending all unresolved blockers in one timeout-prone model request.
- Added workflow-side objection evidence fallback so review objections that omit local evidence refs inherit parent AgentResult/tool evidence before entering Blackboard validation.
- Wrapped Postgres-backed Blackboard mutations in operation-level retry and made Working Memory, commit, and delegation appends idempotent across transient pooler/SSL EOF retries.
- Tightened KnownEvents normalization for generic ISO event times and weak expectation links, preserving quarter/month hints and routing risk/oversupply events to the risk expectation when evidence text clearly supports the override.
- Added a Postgres migration to scope Blackboard objection primary keys by run_id so model-generated objection IDs can repeat across real eval runs without blocking resume/replay.
- Added expectation-detail quality gates for non-empty facts, variables, sourced price reactions, and concrete monitoring events, and disabled O1 tools during field-review objection resolution to reduce resolver timeouts.
- Tightened the expectation-detail prompt and ReAct contract so event monitoring outputs use concrete string triggers instead of generic placeholders or stringified event objects.
- Hardened ReAct expectation-detail normalization so prompt-echo responses are retried, summary-only detail payloads fail schema validation, and construction-only global-research fallback no longer creates empty realized-fact detail patches.
- Added one bounded same-node retry for retryable parallel expectation-detail agent failures so transient model timeouts can recover without discarding successfully cached sibling shells.
- Generalized the bounded retry to all parallel workflow agent jobs, covering BuildGlobalResearch fan-out timeouts as well as expectation-detail retries.
